WEBVTT

00:01:06.212 --> 00:01:09.465
WOULD YOU LIKE TO MEET
YOUR NEXT BOYFRIEND?

00:01:12.468 --> 00:01:15.054
EPISODE 1
THE FUTURES OF YOU AND ME

00:01:33.198 --> 00:01:34.115
2 WEEKS AGO

00:01:34.199 --> 00:01:35.408
I'm home.

00:01:37.493 --> 00:01:38.870
I said I'm home.

00:01:39.662 --> 00:01:41.831
Initiating home mode.

00:01:52.425 --> 00:01:54.052
There's no place like home.

00:02:02.852 --> 00:02:04.270
There are 24 hours in a day.

00:02:06.022 --> 00:02:07.398
Six hours of sleep.

00:02:07.899 --> 00:02:08.942
Ten hours of work.

00:02:09.025 --> 00:02:09.943
COMMUTING: 2 HOURS

00:02:10.026 --> 00:02:11.736
Time spent commuting and eating…

00:02:11.819 --> 00:02:13.488
EATING: 1 HOUR

00:02:13.571 --> 00:02:16.407
Take out all of that, plus washing up,
and I'm left with…

00:02:16.491 --> 00:02:17.700
WASHING UP: 1 HOUR 30 MINUTES

00:02:17.784 --> 00:02:19.661
…just three and a half hours.

00:02:20.703 --> 00:02:23.539
Enough to watch a movie or two, at best.

00:02:25.833 --> 00:02:30.672
I don't waste those precious
three and a half hours on just anyone.

00:02:39.222 --> 00:02:43.184
An ordinary day like today,
with no plans or special events…

00:02:43.893 --> 00:02:44.978
So warm.

00:02:55.697 --> 00:02:58.116
Days like these are the best kind for me.

00:02:58.616 --> 00:02:59.784
Off to sleep now.

00:03:00.326 --> 00:03:02.578
Initiating sleep mode.

00:03:15.133 --> 00:03:17.218
When the brief happiness ends,

00:03:17.302 --> 00:03:20.096
my body is thrown back
into the bustling world.

00:03:26.227 --> 00:03:28.813
The circle route train is arriving.

00:04:13.274 --> 00:04:16.569
Last summer in the Philippines
was the best.

00:04:18.196 --> 00:04:19.864
I wish I could go swimming.

00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:22.784
When is summer coming?

00:04:38.049 --> 00:04:39.175
Excuse me.

00:04:41.094 --> 00:04:42.136
Yes?

00:04:42.220 --> 00:04:43.763
I think that kid just…

00:04:51.771 --> 00:04:54.065
Damn, that little rascal!

00:05:00.363 --> 00:05:01.656
Doors opening.

00:05:07.703 --> 00:05:09.247
Doors opening.

00:05:14.877 --> 00:05:16.587
Doors closing.

00:05:19.048 --> 00:05:19.882
Hello.

00:05:21.050 --> 00:05:21.884
Hey.

00:05:26.305 --> 00:05:27.390
Come on.

00:05:29.016 --> 00:05:29.976
That won't work.

00:05:32.979 --> 00:05:33.813
Okay.

00:05:36.149 --> 00:05:37.316
What's his deal?

00:05:38.734 --> 00:05:40.570
Doors opening.

00:05:45.533 --> 00:05:47.285
Doors closing.

00:05:53.374 --> 00:05:54.584
UNREGISTERED ID

00:05:54.667 --> 00:05:56.669
Please try again.

00:06:08.389 --> 00:06:09.223
Producer?

00:06:09.807 --> 00:06:10.641
Hello.

00:06:10.725 --> 00:06:11.976
-You're here.
-Hi.

00:06:12.059 --> 00:06:13.603
Congratulations.

00:06:13.686 --> 00:06:15.605
-What for…
-Congratulations.

00:06:20.693 --> 00:06:21.736
Thank you.

00:06:25.364 --> 00:06:27.867
As always,
another perfectly punctual arrival.

00:06:27.950 --> 00:06:30.912
Your commitment to never being early
is truly impressive.

00:06:31.412 --> 00:06:33.247
Is it Park Kyeong-nam's birthday today?

00:06:33.331 --> 00:06:34.499
Oh, that?

00:06:34.582 --> 00:06:37.168
-He signed an adaptation deal.
-Again?

00:06:37.251 --> 00:06:40.963
Just come to dinner. The director
is treating us to beef because of that.

00:06:41.047 --> 00:06:42.256
Company dinner?

00:06:43.716 --> 00:06:45.676
I actually have plans today.

00:06:45.760 --> 00:06:47.970
Plans, you say?

00:06:48.054 --> 00:06:50.056
Just say you're going vegetarian instead.

00:06:50.139 --> 00:06:53.351
Mr. Park will be coming, won't he?
He's the man of the hour.

00:06:53.434 --> 00:06:55.311
Even he wouldn't sit this one out.

00:06:55.811 --> 00:06:57.146
Are you really not coming?

00:06:57.647 --> 00:07:02.193
The director is totally miffed
that you've been skipping dinners lately.

00:07:02.276 --> 00:07:04.278
It's not like I'm the only one. That guy…

00:07:04.779 --> 00:07:06.739
Producer Park always skips them too.

00:07:06.822 --> 00:07:09.659
You have a point.
He's a tiny bit less personable than you.

00:07:09.742 --> 00:07:11.536
Don't you think he's so charming?

00:07:12.537 --> 00:07:13.538
Huh?

00:07:15.915 --> 00:07:18.834
Leave her be.
She's been fangirling over Kyeong-nam.

00:07:20.211 --> 00:07:21.462
-Fangirling?
-Yes.

00:07:21.963 --> 00:07:24.799
After much deliberation,
I've decided to give liking him a go.

00:07:26.968 --> 00:07:29.971
What are you talking about?
You've decided to what? Why?

00:07:30.054 --> 00:07:31.514
He's so handsome.

00:07:33.933 --> 00:07:34.809
Smells good too.

00:07:34.892 --> 00:07:36.143
Oh my.

00:07:37.270 --> 00:07:40.523
Eun-ju, you've still got much to learn.

00:07:40.606 --> 00:07:41.440
About what?

00:07:42.024 --> 00:07:46.445
"Never date someone on your own turf,
even with a knife at your throat."

00:07:46.529 --> 00:07:47.738
No one told you that?

00:07:48.864 --> 00:07:51.742
Well, I never said I wanted to date him.

00:07:54.954 --> 00:07:56.372
You'll know when you know.

00:07:56.455 --> 00:07:58.499
-Good luck, Eun-ju.
-Oh dear.

00:08:01.961 --> 00:08:02.795
PARK KYEONG-NAM

00:08:02.878 --> 00:08:06.173
Here is the requested feedback
on your team's proposal from last week.

00:08:06.757 --> 00:08:08.509
Oh, right.

00:08:10.052 --> 00:08:10.970
Weaknesses.

00:08:11.053 --> 00:08:13.055
The protagonist lacks compelling appeal.

00:08:13.139 --> 00:08:15.057
An insufficient grasp
of the fantasy genre.

00:08:15.141 --> 00:08:17.810
Disconnected characters
and unclear themes.

00:08:17.893 --> 00:08:20.730
The story offers
neither universality nor plausibility.

00:08:20.813 --> 00:08:23.024
Strengths. None worth mentioning.

00:08:31.866 --> 00:08:33.701
Hey, Cho!

00:08:34.201 --> 00:08:37.246
Hey, I'm not done talking to you!

00:08:41.459 --> 00:08:42.293
Well,

00:08:42.835 --> 00:08:43.961
I'm done working here.

00:08:44.879 --> 00:08:47.048
-Wait, Mr. Cho!
-Hey! You're quitting?

00:08:47.131 --> 00:08:49.008
-That's right!
-Come on now.

00:08:49.091 --> 00:08:50.885
-Let go.
-You know how he is!

00:08:50.968 --> 00:08:52.637
-I don't care.
-Just think it over.

00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:53.721
No. Move aside!

00:08:53.804 --> 00:08:56.223
Mr. Cho! Wait a minute. Mr. Cho!

00:08:57.391 --> 00:08:58.809
Is he seriously leaving?

00:09:04.106 --> 00:09:06.984
Why are you all looking at me?
I didn't do anything wrong.

00:09:08.235 --> 00:09:11.072
Did he really go? What do we do now?

00:09:11.155 --> 00:09:12.573
JI-YEON

00:09:12.657 --> 00:09:15.493
We really need to meet up today.
I'm serious.

00:09:15.576 --> 00:09:16.827
What's up with her?

00:09:20.498 --> 00:09:21.582
Hey.

00:09:22.083 --> 00:09:23.084
Seo Mi-rae!

00:09:24.126 --> 00:09:25.586
It took me ages to get here.

00:09:29.340 --> 00:09:31.842
Did you call me here
just to drag me around shopping?

00:09:31.926 --> 00:09:34.845
Of course not.
You know I know your lifestyle.

00:09:34.929 --> 00:09:38.599
I called you here to address
a very serious and important issue.

00:09:39.100 --> 00:09:41.352
Issue? What is it?

00:09:42.770 --> 00:09:44.772
An Da-yeong's wedding.
What are you wearing?

00:09:46.190 --> 00:09:47.024
Huh?

00:09:48.359 --> 00:09:52.154
You're not just going to send her money
and be done with it, are you?

00:09:52.947 --> 00:09:55.366
I mean, I'm busy with work and all--

00:09:55.449 --> 00:09:57.618
Hey! All the more reason to go.

00:09:57.702 --> 00:10:01.539
You should be there, dressed to kill,
to show everyone that you're going places!

00:10:01.622 --> 00:10:02.957
I'm going places?

00:10:03.457 --> 00:10:05.418
I mean, that's how you should look.

00:10:05.501 --> 00:10:07.253
All our classmates are gonna be there.

00:10:07.336 --> 00:10:11.173
You can't just sit and watch You-mi
and Se-june pull that lovey-dovey crap.

00:10:11.257 --> 00:10:14.635
Breaking them up isn't an option,
but you should still strut your stuff.

00:10:14.719 --> 00:10:16.387
"I'm totally doing well right now."

00:10:16.470 --> 00:10:17.471
"I'm at my peak."

00:10:17.555 --> 00:10:22.351
Hey, it's been forever since we broke up.
Besides, I have nothing to brag about.

00:10:22.435 --> 00:10:24.478
Hey, this one looks decent.

00:10:24.562 --> 00:10:26.105
Go try this one on.

00:10:26.772 --> 00:10:27.815
Hurry up!

00:10:35.823 --> 00:10:38.826
It's not even Kim Se-june's wedding.
She's so dramatic.

00:10:43.539 --> 00:10:46.375
Don't you dare return that.
I'm so gonna get you.

00:10:46.459 --> 00:10:49.545
Oh, please! You're making it sound
like you bought it for me.

00:10:49.628 --> 00:10:52.840
Hey, I'm an art teacher.
You think I'm rolling in cash?

00:10:52.923 --> 00:10:55.384
I wish I could get you stuff like that.

00:10:57.803 --> 00:10:59.805
Mi-rae, you poor thing.

00:11:00.556 --> 00:11:02.683
Hey, why would you say that?

00:11:03.184 --> 00:11:05.936
I'm doing well. I'm happy, you know.

00:11:06.020 --> 00:11:07.188
Aren't you lonely?

00:11:07.772 --> 00:11:08.898
Not one bit.

00:11:11.275 --> 00:11:14.612
You don't think about guys at all?
For real?

00:11:14.695 --> 00:11:17.948
Would my company give me a raise
if I got myself a boyfriend?

00:11:18.032 --> 00:11:19.158
Doubt that.

00:11:19.241 --> 00:11:22.912
Doesn't that mean dating someone
would only tire me out more

00:11:22.995 --> 00:11:24.413
and make me poorer?

00:11:24.997 --> 00:11:27.291
Getting physically tired
isn't the only problem.

00:11:27.374 --> 00:11:31.921
You know how mentally exhausting it can be
if you end up with an immature guy.

00:11:32.004 --> 00:11:35.132
Then find yourself a mature guy!

00:11:35.216 --> 00:11:37.551
Or someone exactly like you.

00:11:38.135 --> 00:11:40.429
What, a guy like me?

00:11:40.513 --> 00:11:41.514
Yeah!

00:11:41.597 --> 00:11:44.183
-You know, your kind.
-What kind?

00:11:44.266 --> 00:11:48.354
You don't exactly bother others,
but you come off as kinda

00:11:49.313 --> 00:11:50.815
standoffish.

00:11:51.398 --> 00:11:52.858
Date a guy like that.

00:11:53.359 --> 00:11:54.360
Damn.

00:11:55.402 --> 00:11:56.821
I'm done working here.

00:11:56.904 --> 00:11:58.322
Wait, Mr. Cho!

00:11:58.405 --> 00:12:00.115
-You know how he is.
-I don't care.

00:12:00.199 --> 00:12:01.867
What are we gonna do without you?

00:12:01.951 --> 00:12:03.744
Whatever. Ask the director!

00:12:03.828 --> 00:12:05.746
Hey! Are you out of your mind?

00:12:05.830 --> 00:12:07.414
Why would I do that?

00:12:07.498 --> 00:12:11.085
A person's got to be personable.
That's what makes us human.

00:12:12.336 --> 00:12:14.380
So you know how I feel about you!

00:12:20.719 --> 00:12:22.388
Hey, I'm home.

00:12:24.765 --> 00:12:26.267
I said I'm home!

00:12:26.767 --> 00:12:28.644
Initiating home mode.

00:12:47.872 --> 00:12:51.041
God, I must have been out of my mind.

00:13:09.351 --> 00:13:10.436
Are you serious?

00:13:10.519 --> 00:13:11.353
Oh my God.

00:13:11.854 --> 00:13:15.107
What a shame. Mr. Cho was so close
to becoming team leader.

00:13:15.941 --> 00:13:17.192
Was it because of Yun Song?

00:13:18.068 --> 00:13:19.904
Man, who's going to take that on?

00:13:19.987 --> 00:13:20.821
PLANNING TEAM 2

00:13:20.905 --> 00:13:23.490
Did they find a replacement?
Will Team 1 be taking over?

00:13:24.575 --> 00:13:25.576
Word is,

00:13:26.076 --> 00:13:28.913
they're considering
Park Kyeong-nam or Seo Mi-rae.

00:13:29.788 --> 00:13:32.291
What? I get Park Kyeong-nam.

00:13:32.374 --> 00:13:34.919
But Mi-rae?
She's not even in charge of Yun's genre.

00:13:35.002 --> 00:13:36.962
The romance producers
are refusing to do it.

00:13:38.255 --> 00:13:40.507
Mi-rae's schedule is lighter right now.

00:13:41.675 --> 00:13:42.885
Good morning.

00:13:46.430 --> 00:13:48.515
What? What is it?

00:13:59.610 --> 00:14:00.611
What?

00:14:00.694 --> 00:14:01.862
Me? Me? Me?!

00:14:06.158 --> 00:14:08.243
Morning, everyone!

00:14:08.327 --> 00:14:09.370
Good morning!

00:14:09.870 --> 00:14:10.788
Good morning.

00:14:14.249 --> 00:14:17.086
Still, Park Kyeong-nam's been doing
better than you lately.

00:14:17.169 --> 00:14:19.505
The director might assign him
instead of you.

00:14:21.548 --> 00:14:24.802
Well, you never know.
Who knows what the director is thinking?

00:14:29.890 --> 00:14:31.016
Don't worry about it.

00:14:33.727 --> 00:14:35.229
Oh God.

00:14:38.273 --> 00:14:39.650
Ms. Yun!

00:14:41.568 --> 00:14:42.611
Ms. Yun!

00:14:42.695 --> 00:14:44.863
Please open the door, Ms. Yun!

00:14:46.865 --> 00:14:50.202
Ms. Yun! Please give me the final files!

00:14:50.285 --> 00:14:52.287
Ms. Yun!

00:14:59.545 --> 00:15:01.130
Ms. Yun!

00:15:02.131 --> 00:15:03.007
YUN SONG

00:15:07.511 --> 00:15:09.263
WEBTOON "THE MAN TO KNOW"
EPISODE 21

00:15:12.224 --> 00:15:13.058
UPLOAD COMPLETE

00:15:16.520 --> 00:15:20.107
Like a flu virus that slips past
even the raging white blood cells,

00:15:20.607 --> 00:15:24.903
Yun Song, back in the day,
completely took over my daily life.

00:15:30.617 --> 00:15:31.994
YUN SONG

00:15:36.206 --> 00:15:37.374
Yes, Ms. Yun.

00:15:37.458 --> 00:15:38.625
Ms. Seo?

00:15:41.378 --> 00:15:43.672
Ms. Yun, are you crying?

00:15:44.214 --> 00:15:45.632
Did you see the comments?

00:15:46.300 --> 00:15:48.969
The things they wrote about me!

00:15:50.679 --> 00:15:53.098
Ms. Yun, it's 3:00 a.m. right now.

00:15:53.182 --> 00:15:56.685
These hateful comments won't stop
until I die, will they?

00:15:56.769 --> 00:16:00.314
But why should I?
Why should I be the one to go?

00:16:00.397 --> 00:16:02.483
You sons of bitches!

00:16:05.069 --> 00:16:06.070
No!

00:16:06.612 --> 00:16:08.113
Absolutely not.

00:16:25.589 --> 00:16:27.925
IN

00:16:28.008 --> 00:16:29.843
Director, it's Seo Mi-rae.

00:16:29.927 --> 00:16:31.220
Yes, come in.

00:16:34.306 --> 00:16:37.392
I happened to pass by Raturer Macaron
after having lunch.

00:16:37.476 --> 00:16:39.228
I know how much you love…

00:16:44.858 --> 00:16:47.903
I see you were also here, Mr. Park.

00:16:47.986 --> 00:16:51.115
Yes. I also happened
to pass by that place.

00:16:52.199 --> 00:16:54.118
Take a seat. We can talk together.

00:16:57.996 --> 00:17:00.582
God, that's sweet. Too sweet!

00:17:00.666 --> 00:17:02.709
-Have some coffee.
-Okay.

00:17:07.089 --> 00:17:08.924
This coffee you got… You got…

00:17:09.675 --> 00:17:11.510
-Yirgacheffe.
-You got Cheffe!

00:17:11.593 --> 00:17:13.387
Right, Cheffe.

00:17:14.763 --> 00:17:19.226
Man, I didn't realize
how sociable you guys are until today.

00:17:20.269 --> 00:17:21.603
I need to talk to you about--

00:17:21.687 --> 00:17:22.771
Now!

00:17:23.939 --> 00:17:26.984
An opportunity like this
won't ever come around again, okay?

00:17:27.067 --> 00:17:28.735
Make your case for why

00:17:29.236 --> 00:17:34.449
you should be put in charge of managing
Yun Song, Naemo's number-one author.

00:17:34.533 --> 00:17:36.034
Right. I'd first like to--

00:17:36.118 --> 00:17:40.455
Even though you two heartlessly declined
to attend any of the dinners,

00:17:41.039 --> 00:17:42.875
this is no place for personal grudges.

00:17:42.958 --> 00:17:46.211
I'll decide based solely on your skills.

00:17:46.712 --> 00:17:49.631
So just relax. And speak up.

00:17:50.215 --> 00:17:51.466
What I'm saying is,

00:17:51.550 --> 00:17:55.179
the right person to manage
our top author is none other than--

00:17:55.262 --> 00:17:56.263
I'll step aside.

00:17:57.890 --> 00:17:59.975
I may have joined Naemo a bit earlier,

00:18:00.058 --> 00:18:04.646
but Ms. Seo's shown she's capable
of managing authors and planning projects.

00:18:04.730 --> 00:18:09.151
No matter how I think about it,
I think you should grab that opportunity.

00:18:09.234 --> 00:18:10.277
All right, then.

00:18:10.360 --> 00:18:13.739
No. I wouldn't dare take the place
of someone so competent

00:18:13.822 --> 00:18:16.408
and manage Ms. Yun for the second time.

00:18:16.491 --> 00:18:17.701
You're being too modest.

00:18:17.784 --> 00:18:21.496
Mr. Park gets a hit
out of every author he manages.

00:18:21.580 --> 00:18:23.415
He'd be perfect for Ms. Yun.

00:18:23.498 --> 00:18:26.376
Besides, in his own words,

00:18:27.127 --> 00:18:29.588
my projects have
no strengths worth mentioning.

00:18:31.131 --> 00:18:35.052
Ms. Yun's already set the whole table,
so there's not much to worry about.

00:18:35.135 --> 00:18:38.180
Wow, then you should sit at that table
and dig in.

00:18:38.263 --> 00:18:39.223
Enough.

00:18:40.432 --> 00:18:45.020
So, neither of you wants to do it.
That's the gist of it, no?

00:18:47.439 --> 00:18:48.899
Fine, I get it.

00:18:51.360 --> 00:18:52.361
But still,

00:18:52.444 --> 00:18:55.572
how can you work in the webtoon business
with so little passion?

00:18:57.199 --> 00:18:59.451
You guys worship work-life balance,
don't you?

00:19:00.244 --> 00:19:01.703
Forget it. We're all done here.

00:19:04.206 --> 00:19:05.290
Seo, you manage her.

00:19:06.458 --> 00:19:07.292
What?

00:19:07.376 --> 00:19:09.836
I noticed
you were only managing six authors.

00:19:09.920 --> 00:19:10.963
But--

00:19:11.046 --> 00:19:15.425
Besides, you're the one who directed Yun
toward romance when she started out.

00:19:15.509 --> 00:19:18.887
Yes, but I ended up handing it over
to a different producer.

00:19:18.971 --> 00:19:20.222
You know it's not my genre.

00:19:20.305 --> 00:19:21.682
Actually, I don't.

00:19:22.391 --> 00:19:25.394
Then I'll consider this matter settled
and take my leave.

00:19:25.477 --> 00:19:27.771
-I have a meeting to attend.
-Sure. Go ahead.

00:19:27.854 --> 00:19:28.689
All right.

00:19:29.314 --> 00:19:30.315
I'll leave you to it.

00:19:34.653 --> 00:19:35.654
Excuse me.

00:19:41.535 --> 00:19:43.120
A meeting just magically popped up?

00:19:44.705 --> 00:19:45.956
Off you go.

00:19:54.589 --> 00:19:55.757
You call that a meeting?

00:19:59.052 --> 00:20:00.012
How did it go?

00:20:04.474 --> 00:20:05.475
So it's you?

00:20:08.729 --> 00:20:11.857
Park Kyeong-nam showed up
with a whole box of macarons.

00:20:12.482 --> 00:20:14.484
-Wonder who tipped him off.
-What?

00:20:15.193 --> 00:20:17.070
Hey, it wasn't me.

00:20:17.654 --> 00:20:19.197
Well, so,

00:20:19.781 --> 00:20:22.326
how long will you be
in charge of Ms. Yun Song?

00:20:24.119 --> 00:20:26.079
-Dunno.
-How long?

00:20:26.163 --> 00:20:28.707
Until she collapses from exhaustion.

00:20:29.333 --> 00:20:31.251
Mi-rae, you've got this.

00:20:31.335 --> 00:20:34.338
Don't let it get you down.
You just need to get the jump on her.

00:20:34.421 --> 00:20:36.340
Like that will work with Yun Song.

00:20:37.090 --> 00:20:41.011
Some pasts come back to you,
reborn as the future.

00:20:41.511 --> 00:20:42.596
Didn't I tell you?

00:20:42.679 --> 00:20:45.349
My sister's friend works
at Dongseoyang Law Firm.

00:20:45.432 --> 00:20:47.601
-I'm heading there tomorrow.
-You just got back?

00:20:47.684 --> 00:20:49.519
-Stupid online trolls.
-What?

00:20:49.603 --> 00:20:52.814
-I'm gonna confront them this time.
-Be quiet. Ms. Yun's on the phone.

00:20:52.898 --> 00:20:54.691
Settlement? Not on your life.

00:20:54.775 --> 00:20:56.526
-Does she ever sleep?
-I have money.

00:20:56.610 --> 00:20:58.945
-I'm calling my sister now.
-She's really something.

00:21:02.532 --> 00:21:03.492
She hung up!

00:21:04.826 --> 00:21:06.578
I'm really going crazy.

00:21:06.661 --> 00:21:08.205
Are you sure you can come tonight?

00:21:09.289 --> 00:21:11.375
You bet. It's your birthday.

00:21:11.458 --> 00:21:14.127
The advertisement we talked about,
is it a go or not?

00:21:14.211 --> 00:21:15.962
You don't need to worry too much.

00:21:16.046 --> 00:21:18.382
Of course I need to worry.
We're talking money here.

00:21:18.465 --> 00:21:20.217
I'll sort it out, Ms. Yun.

00:21:20.300 --> 00:21:23.845
I've been so busy writing.
I can't do anything, let alone eat.

00:21:23.929 --> 00:21:25.389
Do you know how hard that is?

00:21:25.472 --> 00:21:27.140
I know how hard it must be.

00:21:27.224 --> 00:21:29.267
-Can I take a break this month?
-What?

00:21:29.351 --> 00:21:31.686
But you already took a break last month.

00:21:31.770 --> 00:21:35.899
Why do those damn trolls keep
driving me crazy over every little thing?

00:21:35.982 --> 00:21:37.818
It's so frustrating!

00:21:38.318 --> 00:21:39.903
Don't mind those hateful comments.

00:21:47.202 --> 00:21:48.620
SE-JUNE

00:21:53.333 --> 00:21:57.421
The person you are calling is unavailable.
Please leave a message.

00:22:06.638 --> 00:22:07.848
SE-JUNE
12 MISSED CALLS

00:22:07.931 --> 00:22:08.765
Crap!

00:22:14.396 --> 00:22:15.564
Oh no.

00:22:17.691 --> 00:22:18.692
Come on!

00:22:28.326 --> 00:22:32.706
That's how my romance became a past
that would never come back.

00:22:36.585 --> 00:22:40.172
Forget clocking out on time.
You'll be lucky to catch the last train.

00:22:40.255 --> 00:22:45.594
Didn't you get a bald spot here before
from stressing about Yun Song?

00:22:45.677 --> 00:22:47.179
Let's see if it's grown back.

00:22:47.262 --> 00:22:49.473
-She did?
-I think it was around here.

00:22:50.474 --> 00:22:53.351
-Was it this side?
-It's gonna fall out again anyway.

00:22:53.894 --> 00:22:56.146
Hey, guys. Cut it out.

00:22:57.230 --> 00:22:59.149
You had something to tell me, Hye-bin?

00:22:59.649 --> 00:23:00.734
Oh, yeah…

00:23:02.819 --> 00:23:05.530
Will you be attending
the meeting with the author?

00:23:16.708 --> 00:23:18.210
That hurts!

00:23:18.752 --> 00:23:21.296
My goodness, I'm sorry! I didn't mean to.

00:23:21.379 --> 00:23:22.714
Miss, are you okay?

00:23:29.930 --> 00:23:32.849
-She's so pretty!
-Yes. You've gotten prettier.

00:23:32.933 --> 00:23:33.850
What a glow-up.

00:23:33.934 --> 00:23:35.602
Have you lost weight?

00:23:36.603 --> 00:23:40.148
What the heck?
Hey, I told you not to return that outfit.

00:23:40.232 --> 00:23:42.734
-I didn't return it.
-Then why didn't you wear it?

00:23:43.527 --> 00:23:47.364
No reason. I didn't feel like it.
There's no point in looking good today.

00:23:47.447 --> 00:23:49.741
-But--
-Seo Mi-rae!

00:23:49.824 --> 00:23:51.618
Hey, you only answer Ji-yeon's calls!

00:23:51.701 --> 00:23:53.828
Didn't think I'd see you.
I heard you were busy.

00:23:53.912 --> 00:23:55.247
It's so nice to get together.

00:23:55.330 --> 00:23:56.456
How have you been?

00:23:56.540 --> 00:23:58.375
I've got so much to tell you.

00:23:58.458 --> 00:24:00.126
Let's talk over drinks later.

00:24:00.669 --> 00:24:01.503
Let's go.

00:24:01.586 --> 00:24:02.796
Please welcome the groom!

00:24:12.305 --> 00:24:16.977
The cliché of awkwardly running into
your ex at a mutual friend's wedding

00:24:18.436 --> 00:24:20.438
never happened, after all.

00:24:20.522 --> 00:24:24.192
Today's true star will be entering now.
Please welcome the bride.

00:24:27.654 --> 00:24:29.072
Da-yeong!

00:24:29.781 --> 00:24:31.616
-Congratulations!
-Beautiful.

00:24:39.457 --> 00:24:41.459
Congratulations!

00:24:41.543 --> 00:24:43.211
Congrats. Be happy!

00:24:43.295 --> 00:24:44.921
You look great together!

00:24:46.464 --> 00:24:47.674
You look like a goddess!

00:24:54.222 --> 00:24:55.682
She was stunning, wasn't she?

00:24:55.765 --> 00:24:57.142
-Yeah.
-She really was.

00:24:57.225 --> 00:24:59.978
We'll be having drinks later.
You're coming, right?

00:25:00.061 --> 00:25:02.564
Definitely. I'll make sure
to bring Mi-rae along.

00:25:02.647 --> 00:25:03.732
-Good.
-Be right back.

00:25:03.815 --> 00:25:05.358
You'd better come this time.

00:25:05.442 --> 00:25:08.153
-Got it.
-You always skip out.

00:25:09.613 --> 00:25:10.864
You-mi!

00:25:11.364 --> 00:25:12.532
You-mi! Congratulations!

00:25:12.616 --> 00:25:14.618
-Is that You-mi?
-Where?

00:25:16.119 --> 00:25:17.370
Hey, you!

00:25:19.205 --> 00:25:21.374
-Did you hear? She's getting married.
-Really?

00:25:21.458 --> 00:25:22.667
-I am.
-No way!

00:25:22.751 --> 00:25:26.046
-Is Se-june still in America?
-Yes. He's coming next week.

00:25:26.129 --> 00:25:28.131
Hey, when you get married…

00:25:30.175 --> 00:25:36.097
A girlfriend who would be the envy of all,
and a sparkling diamond ring on her hand.

00:25:42.729 --> 00:25:48.485
He managed to show off what he had
without even showing his face once.

00:25:49.277 --> 00:25:50.904
-Congrats!
-I'm happy for you.

00:25:50.987 --> 00:25:53.156
You're even prettier.
Is it the engagement glow?

00:25:53.239 --> 00:25:55.075
Stop it! You're all pretty.

00:26:08.838 --> 00:26:11.508
I'd love to carry my kid like that
after I get married.

00:26:13.093 --> 00:26:14.135
You wanna get married?

00:26:15.011 --> 00:26:17.681
-I'm sure I will someday.
-To whom?

00:26:21.059 --> 00:26:23.061
Whatever. I'm sure
you'll find someone someday.

00:26:23.687 --> 00:26:25.689
Hey, what's up with you?

00:26:26.356 --> 00:26:27.399
What do you mean?

00:26:27.899 --> 00:26:29.275
Why are you talking like that?

00:26:29.359 --> 00:26:33.029
Every time we bring up the future,
you always start with "I."

00:26:33.988 --> 00:26:36.408
Have you ever said "we" first?

00:27:00.557 --> 00:27:04.060
We haven't met in a while.
Looking forward to catching up tomorrow.

00:27:04.144 --> 00:27:06.521
Are you freaking kidding me?

00:27:06.604 --> 00:27:08.231
I'd forgotten about this.

00:27:08.898 --> 00:27:12.485
Seriously, why are you all
doing this to me?

00:27:14.279 --> 00:27:15.488
THE MAN TO KNOW

00:27:16.656 --> 00:27:17.991
EPISODE 107

00:27:18.074 --> 00:27:20.118
HOW DARE YOU…
MAKE A MOVE ON MY FAMILY?!

00:27:20.618 --> 00:27:21.453
SQUEEZE

00:27:21.953 --> 00:27:23.872
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YOU DISAPPOINT ME, AUNT

00:27:24.372 --> 00:27:28.042
So she's gone even more off the rails
since the last time.

00:27:30.462 --> 00:27:32.964
Naemo's most popular webtoon
for three years running,

00:27:33.047 --> 00:27:35.508
Yun Song's The Man to Know.

00:27:35.592 --> 00:27:39.512
A chaebol romance featuring Choi Si-woo,
the third-generation heir of SY Group.

00:27:39.596 --> 00:27:42.557
Of course, he's just as disrespectful
as he is handsome,

00:27:42.640 --> 00:27:46.770
with the classic and clichéd selling point
of only being soft with the female lead.

00:27:46.853 --> 00:27:50.982
It's a romance-action hodgepodge mixed
with all the intrigue of a chaebol family.

00:27:51.483 --> 00:27:53.693
The main romance plot is so clichéd

00:27:53.777 --> 00:27:57.781
that Hans Christian Andersen would rise
from the grave and sue her for plagiarism.

00:27:58.281 --> 00:28:00.700
While in Cebu
for a resort construction project,

00:28:00.784 --> 00:28:03.828
Choi Si-woo goes surfing one morning,
is swept away by the waves,

00:28:03.912 --> 00:28:07.624
only to be rescued by Eun Na-ra,
the female protagonist on vacation,

00:28:07.707 --> 00:28:10.043
and falls in love with her.

00:28:13.004 --> 00:28:13.838
THE MAN TO KNOW

00:28:13.922 --> 00:28:15.131
YS is such a has-been.

00:28:15.215 --> 00:28:17.801
Waste of money.
Treat your folks to dinner instead.

00:28:17.884 --> 00:28:19.135
How is this number one?

00:28:19.219 --> 00:28:20.845
Naemo fell off. Fire YS already.

00:28:20.929 --> 00:28:22.597
Manage your authors better.

00:28:22.680 --> 00:28:25.058
Great fix for low BP.
It got me all worked up.

00:28:25.141 --> 00:28:27.811
YS should quit Instagram first.
I feel sorry for her fans.

00:28:28.311 --> 00:28:29.479
YUN SONG

00:28:30.271 --> 00:28:32.273
Yun Song debates with readers again.

00:28:32.357 --> 00:28:34.901
Yun Song faces backlash
after posting targeted message.

00:28:34.984 --> 00:28:37.987
Fans angered by popular author
Yun Song's unprofessional hiatus.

00:28:54.420 --> 00:28:55.547
Here for snacks?

00:28:56.923 --> 00:28:57.757
No, I just…

00:29:09.519 --> 00:29:10.979
That annoying jerk.

00:29:12.146 --> 00:29:13.231
That selfish jerk.

00:29:14.274 --> 00:29:16.025
That self-centered jerk.

00:29:16.109 --> 00:29:18.236
-Ms. Seo.
-Yes?

00:29:20.321 --> 00:29:21.656
How long are you gonna be on that?

00:29:24.742 --> 00:29:26.661
Just five more minutes.

00:29:28.746 --> 00:29:29.581
Sure.

00:30:08.202 --> 00:30:09.787
Lovely weather today.

00:30:17.962 --> 00:30:20.882
Ms. Seo, about the handover
of Ms. Yun's work…

00:30:20.965 --> 00:30:22.884
Oh, right. Who's handing over to me?

00:30:22.967 --> 00:30:24.302
From Mr. Park.

00:30:25.345 --> 00:30:26.346
Sorry?

00:30:27.764 --> 00:30:29.599
Mr. Park?

00:30:37.190 --> 00:30:40.401
What was this doing here?
Did you miss it because it's so small?

00:30:43.154 --> 00:30:45.406
I'm here for the handover.

00:30:45.907 --> 00:30:47.992
Oh, the handover.

00:30:52.246 --> 00:30:53.623
Five minutes.

00:30:54.374 --> 00:30:55.208
Conference room.

00:30:56.626 --> 00:30:58.586
-Five minutes?
-Yes.

00:31:00.630 --> 00:31:01.631
All right.

00:31:08.596 --> 00:31:12.183
It has the lowest ratings,
but the sales are still steady.

00:31:12.266 --> 00:31:14.143
We have three ad deals remaining.

00:31:14.811 --> 00:31:17.563
Let's move one to a branded webtoon
by next month.

00:31:17.647 --> 00:31:19.357
The CTR is pretty good,

00:31:19.440 --> 00:31:21.985
so we can push that point
when contacting future clients.

00:31:22.568 --> 00:31:25.780
Bet you feel great after dumping
this ticking time bomb on me.

00:31:25.863 --> 00:31:28.199
Could you take a look
at the file I'm sending you?

00:31:32.912 --> 00:31:35.415
Man, look how neat his nails are.

00:31:35.915 --> 00:31:37.709
Not a single cuticle in sight.

00:31:37.792 --> 00:31:38.835
-Ms. Seo.
-Yes?

00:31:40.962 --> 00:31:41.963
Please accept it.

00:31:44.757 --> 00:31:45.883
Okay.

00:31:45.967 --> 00:31:50.263
This is the feedback my team has shared
with Mr. Cho on The Man to Know so far.

00:31:50.346 --> 00:31:52.390
-Take a look if you need to.
-Okay.

00:31:52.890 --> 00:31:53.891
And…

00:31:58.271 --> 00:32:02.358
PARK KYEONG-NAM SENT A MESSAGE
SAUNA COUPON

00:32:02.442 --> 00:32:03.276
What's this?

00:32:04.694 --> 00:32:06.612
Mr. Cho said you'd need it.

00:32:08.656 --> 00:32:12.035
I don't need it.
I'll be sleeping at home, no matter what.

00:32:13.578 --> 00:32:15.329
Okay. Sure.

00:32:16.706 --> 00:32:19.459
Anyway, that's all for the handover.

00:32:20.043 --> 00:32:21.294
Any questions?

00:32:22.754 --> 00:32:23.588
No.

00:32:24.422 --> 00:32:25.631
Right, then.

00:32:42.648 --> 00:32:43.775
Time for lunch.

00:32:46.319 --> 00:32:47.320
Is it already?

00:32:48.613 --> 00:32:50.323
Today's your first meeting with Yun.

00:32:51.282 --> 00:32:53.117
Let's go. I'll treat you to unadon.

00:32:54.660 --> 00:32:56.954
You're the best.

00:33:00.625 --> 00:33:01.959
-Let's go.
-Let's go!

00:33:02.460 --> 00:33:05.630
Eating ginger makes me nauseous
for some reason.

00:33:05.713 --> 00:33:07.131
She just doesn't get it.

00:33:07.215 --> 00:33:09.550
Ginger is what makes unadon so great.

00:33:09.634 --> 00:33:11.052
You got that right!

00:33:12.053 --> 00:33:14.097
I'm starving. We could've ordered in.

00:33:40.373 --> 00:33:41.290
Seo Mi-rae!

00:33:42.291 --> 00:33:44.752
Ms. Yun! You're here early.

00:33:44.836 --> 00:33:48.172
We can eat together before our meeting.
I'm right on time, aren't I?

00:33:48.256 --> 00:33:50.133
You guys go on ahead!

00:33:50.216 --> 00:33:51.801
Come on. I'm hungry!

00:33:52.844 --> 00:33:54.053
-Bye, Mi-rae.
-I'm hungry.

00:33:54.137 --> 00:33:55.388
Enjoy your meal, Ms. Yun.

00:34:20.746 --> 00:34:21.581
It's so good.

00:34:23.666 --> 00:34:27.253
-Worried about working with me?
-Sorry? Not at all.

00:34:28.629 --> 00:34:31.549
If Cho hadn't gotten sick,
we would have kept going.

00:34:31.632 --> 00:34:33.759
It's such a shame he's so frail.

00:34:33.843 --> 00:34:37.763
It was our first reunion in a while,
and she was still as clueless as ever.

00:34:37.847 --> 00:34:39.724
It's been three years. Let's crush it.

00:34:40.308 --> 00:34:43.311
Sure. I look forward to working with you.

00:34:43.895 --> 00:34:47.440
If it weren't for you,
things wouldn't have worked out for me.

00:34:49.901 --> 00:34:52.820
You would've managed fine without me.

00:34:53.988 --> 00:34:55.031
That's true.

00:35:00.369 --> 00:35:04.373
The female lead being constantly tormented
by her in-laws' disapproval,

00:35:04.457 --> 00:35:07.877
only to have Choi Si-woo swoop in,
acting all cool, to save her…

00:35:07.960 --> 00:35:10.630
The readers are getting
a little tired of that.

00:35:11.339 --> 00:35:13.507
Recently, the aunt-in-law
has been a bit too…

00:35:14.008 --> 00:35:15.134
Good grief.

00:35:16.302 --> 00:35:19.555
You want the super-rich, swoony male lead
to drop the cool act?

00:35:21.807 --> 00:35:25.561
That wasn't the point.
The constant disapproval of the family--

00:35:25.645 --> 00:35:28.064
Why do the readers complain
but keep reading anyway?

00:35:28.147 --> 00:35:32.151
Because they just expect me to give them
something to complain about.

00:35:32.860 --> 00:35:37.281
Goodness, this is the kind of thing
I was worried about.

00:35:37.365 --> 00:35:38.282
Sorry?

00:35:39.784 --> 00:35:40.660
What do you mean?

00:35:41.911 --> 00:35:44.580
I know you're smart and all,

00:35:45.081 --> 00:35:48.501
but we both know we don't really vibe.

00:35:52.922 --> 00:35:56.092
Then you could've told the director
you didn't want to work with me.

00:35:56.842 --> 00:36:00.763
I mean, it won't be an issue
as long as we figure things out as we go.

00:36:02.265 --> 00:36:03.641
Just like old times.

00:36:09.855 --> 00:36:11.023
Just like old times.

00:36:11.107 --> 00:36:13.693
Please give me the final files!

00:36:14.193 --> 00:36:15.528
Just like old times.

00:36:16.112 --> 00:36:17.363
Just like old times.

00:36:17.446 --> 00:36:18.948
Ms. Yun!

00:36:21.617 --> 00:36:25.496
I'm sorry to bother you.
A guest would like to see you, Ms. Yun.

00:36:25.579 --> 00:36:27.957
-Is that so? Sure.
-All right.

00:36:28.457 --> 00:36:29.625
-Please come in.
-Hello.

00:36:29.709 --> 00:36:31.294
-Hi. How have you been?
-Hello.

00:36:31.377 --> 00:36:32.336
It's been a while.

00:36:32.420 --> 00:36:36.048
This is Producer Seo Mi-rae,
who will be in charge of Ms. Yun.

00:36:36.132 --> 00:36:37.049
Right.

00:36:37.133 --> 00:36:38.384
-Hello.
-Hello.

00:36:39.552 --> 00:36:40.803
My name is Min Jun-young.

00:36:40.886 --> 00:36:43.389
-I'm Seo Mi-rae. Great to meet you.
-Nice to meet you.

00:36:43.472 --> 00:36:44.807
-Have a seat.
-Thanks.

00:36:46.726 --> 00:36:50.521
So, there's this new dating simulation
that DU just launched,

00:36:50.604 --> 00:36:52.940
and Choi Si-woo was used in it.

00:36:53.024 --> 00:36:55.735
Ms. Yun's already met him
a few times over the contract.

00:36:56.319 --> 00:36:59.655
If it's a dating simulation,
is it like a game?

00:36:59.739 --> 00:37:02.825
It's more like a dating app than a game,
and more realistic.

00:37:04.618 --> 00:37:05.953
So what is it called?

00:37:06.037 --> 00:37:07.038
Boyfriend on Demand.

00:37:11.417 --> 00:37:14.045
See that? I told you she was like this.

00:37:14.128 --> 00:37:16.922
She always cringes
at the slightest sign of cheesiness.

00:37:17.423 --> 00:37:19.425
-No, that's not it. I--
-That's okay.

00:37:19.508 --> 00:37:21.177
Everyone reacts the same way you do.

00:37:23.429 --> 00:37:25.097
I wanted to meet you today, Ms. Yun,

00:37:25.181 --> 00:37:28.517
because our planning team loved
your character so much.

00:37:28.601 --> 00:37:32.605
They suggested using the male leads
from your other works as well.

00:37:33.564 --> 00:37:36.192
-The male leads from my other works?
-Yes.

00:37:37.109 --> 00:37:40.780
That's understandable,
given Choi Si-woo's popularity,

00:37:40.863 --> 00:37:43.699
but the others aren't all that cool.

00:37:43.783 --> 00:37:46.077
You could call them Si-woo knockoffs.

00:37:49.872 --> 00:37:52.375
-Well, they are!
-Isn't she just hilarious?

00:37:52.458 --> 00:37:53.876
What she means is…

00:37:53.959 --> 00:37:58.589
Some of us did say other characters
might not have as much impact as Si-woo,

00:37:58.672 --> 00:38:03.594
so I just wanted to hear your thoughts
before making a formal proposal.

00:38:04.804 --> 00:38:06.055
In that case--

00:38:07.014 --> 00:38:10.101
Then how about using the second male lead?

00:38:11.769 --> 00:38:14.105
-Yes, that's--
-Second male lead?

00:38:14.688 --> 00:38:15.689
Yes, so…

00:38:15.773 --> 00:38:20.444
In her works, the lead and the second lead
always have such different charms,

00:38:20.528 --> 00:38:22.947
so the female lead wavers
until the very end.

00:38:23.030 --> 00:38:23.864
Yes.

00:38:23.948 --> 00:38:26.158
Take Hong-ju from Bloodsucking Boyfriend.

00:38:26.242 --> 00:38:29.578
He was so popular that you ended up
having to kill him off.

00:38:29.662 --> 00:38:30.830
That's right.

00:38:30.913 --> 00:38:34.417
Did the Team Leader Say That?
has a final episode rating of four.

00:38:34.500 --> 00:38:36.794
Fans of the second lead review-bombed it.

00:38:36.877 --> 00:38:37.795
Right.

00:38:38.671 --> 00:38:43.008
You could use the second male lead
in your app with this tagline.

00:38:43.801 --> 00:38:46.720
"It's your turn to make him the lead."

00:38:46.804 --> 00:38:49.014
That would create quite a buzz,
don't you think?

00:38:49.098 --> 00:38:50.641
Wow, I love it!

00:38:51.851 --> 00:38:53.436
Man, that's just, wow…

00:38:56.230 --> 00:38:57.314
"Make him the lead!"

00:38:58.983 --> 00:38:59.984
Nice, huh?

00:39:07.199 --> 00:39:08.742
Doors opening.

00:39:09.869 --> 00:39:12.538
Ms. Yun, please answer your calls
going forward.

00:39:12.621 --> 00:39:13.456
Bye now.

00:39:13.539 --> 00:39:15.708
-Answer them, please!
-Yeah.

00:39:23.424 --> 00:39:24.258
Hi.

00:39:24.341 --> 00:39:26.343
Did you have a good talk
with the director?

00:39:26.427 --> 00:39:27.344
I did, yes.

00:39:27.428 --> 00:39:28.345
Ms. Seo?

00:39:28.846 --> 00:39:31.348
Do you have time for a quick chat?

00:39:32.933 --> 00:39:33.851
Excuse me?

00:39:33.934 --> 00:39:35.603
A product reviewer?

00:39:35.686 --> 00:39:37.771
Yes. It's nothing serious, really.

00:39:37.855 --> 00:39:39.565
You just need to give us a review

00:39:39.648 --> 00:39:42.401
after using the app for a month
with the equipment provided.

00:39:44.278 --> 00:39:47.031
I'm not exactly sure
what I should be reviewing.

00:39:47.823 --> 00:39:51.035
It's a dating app,
so you'll be reviewing your dates.

00:39:51.118 --> 00:39:55.206
Your thoughts on your dates
and what you liked or disliked about them.

00:39:56.207 --> 00:40:00.044
So is it more like role-playing
than an actual date?

00:40:00.127 --> 00:40:02.129
Very realistic role-playing.

00:40:02.755 --> 00:40:05.341
You're not into cheesy stuff,
is that right?

00:40:06.634 --> 00:40:07.468
Yes.

00:40:07.551 --> 00:40:10.596
Our goal is to captivate
people like you as well.

00:40:11.096 --> 00:40:13.098
That, and you seem consumer-savvy.

00:40:13.682 --> 00:40:18.729
Our app is in beta service,
so we're in dire need of quality feedback.

00:40:19.313 --> 00:40:23.108
You will be compensated,
so think it over and get back to us.

00:40:24.151 --> 00:40:25.486
I'd get paid for this?

00:40:25.569 --> 00:40:28.739
Of course.
You'd be putting in your valuable time.

00:40:48.926 --> 00:40:50.761
"Boyfriend on Demand."

00:41:15.744 --> 00:41:18.414
"Sync your phone with the device."

00:41:25.713 --> 00:41:29.466
Transmitting user information
to the device.

00:41:35.931 --> 00:41:39.018
"Place the ring on your head
and assume a comfortable position."

00:41:39.101 --> 00:41:41.854
"The ring will automatically adjust
to the user's head"?

00:41:41.937 --> 00:41:44.773
"You are invited to the world of wonders."

00:41:44.857 --> 00:41:47.151
Personalization process complete.

00:41:47.651 --> 00:41:51.447
Place the ring on your head
and assume a comfortable position.

00:41:56.535 --> 00:41:59.246
Press the red button on the device.

00:41:59.747 --> 00:42:03.584
When you press the button, the ring
will light up and begin connecting.

00:42:09.632 --> 00:42:10.466
What's going on?

00:42:39.536 --> 00:42:40.537
It's cold!

00:43:34.049 --> 00:43:34.967
I can…

00:43:36.093 --> 00:43:37.469
I can breathe.

00:44:31.398 --> 00:44:32.608
What the…

00:44:41.408 --> 00:44:42.367
Wait a second.

00:44:44.036 --> 00:44:45.788
THE MAN TO KNOW

00:44:46.371 --> 00:44:47.372
This is…

00:44:47.456 --> 00:44:49.374
This is Choi Si-woo.

00:44:54.505 --> 00:44:58.300
Congratulations, Ms. Seo Mi-rae,
on meeting your first date!

00:45:05.307 --> 00:45:07.184
Are you okay?

00:48:09.908 --> 00:48:14.913
Subtitle translation by: Daham Yoon